{"data":{"post":{"id":"aab4ff8b-9ba0-52c7-b12d-de60fc7c642c","html":"<h1>Configuring PyCharm</h1>\n<h2>Before you begin</h2>\n<p>Before you get along with this guide, make sure that you’ve <code class=\"language-text\">python</code> and any version of <code class=\"language-text\">PyCharm</code> (community or Professional) installed. If you haven’t install them now.</p>\n<h2>Creating a new project in PyCharm</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Open PyCharm, click on <code class=\"language-text\">Create New Project</code>\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/pycharm_menu-dd5cef4c620ef585358cbdff6166847c-07f73.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 66.81664791901014%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"img\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/pycharm_menu-dd5cef4c620ef585358cbdff6166847c-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/pycharm_menu-dd5cef4c620ef585358cbdff6166847c-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/pycharm_menu-dd5cef4c620ef585358cbdff6166847c-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/pycharm_menu-dd5cef4c620ef585358cbdff6166847c-48538.png 800w,\n/static/pycharm_menu-dd5cef4c620ef585358cbdff6166847c-b70ec.png 1200w,\n/static/pycharm_menu-dd5cef4c620ef585358cbdff6166847c-d134a.png 1600w,\n/static/pycharm_menu-dd5cef4c620ef585358cbdff6166847c-07f73.png 1778w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Next select the directory for your project. Best way is to create the directory on your hard drive first and then just ask <code class=\"language-text\">PyCharm</code> to create project in that directory.\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/pycharm2-882bec98a39047f7e200164c07768a1a-07f73.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 66.81664791901014%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"img\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/pycharm2-882bec98a39047f7e200164c07768a1a-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/pycharm2-882bec98a39047f7e200164c07768a1a-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/pycharm2-882bec98a39047f7e200164c07768a1a-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/pycharm2-882bec98a39047f7e200164c07768a1a-48538.png 800w,\n/static/pycharm2-882bec98a39047f7e200164c07768a1a-b70ec.png 1200w,\n/static/pycharm2-882bec98a39047f7e200164c07768a1a-d134a.png 1600w,\n/static/pycharm2-882bec98a39047f7e200164c07768a1a-07f73.png 1778w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>As you can see, I’ve set the project directory on my desktop inside a folder called <code class=\"language-text\">PyDemo</code>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Now select <code class=\"language-text\">python</code> version you installed. In my case, I’ve multiple versions of <code class=\"language-text\">python</code> installed so it looks like this</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/pycharm3-029052b32a967307b86c751ba311385c-09c26.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 32.83358320839581%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"img\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/pycharm3-029052b32a967307b86c751ba311385c-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/pycharm3-029052b32a967307b86c751ba311385c-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/pycharm3-029052b32a967307b86c751ba311385c-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/pycharm3-029052b32a967307b86c751ba311385c-48538.png 800w,\n/static/pycharm3-029052b32a967307b86c751ba311385c-b70ec.png 1200w,\n/static/pycharm3-029052b32a967307b86c751ba311385c-09c26.png 1334w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>In your case, you just pick the one you’ve installed. Now what if your python installation doesn’t show up? Click on the gear button and select your python installation directory from there. <code class=\"language-text\">PyCharm</code> will index it so you can use the python installation for any project later on.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/pc41-e96a0c65d1a2ef1a2e1a18a6008d582f-7e945.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 16.640746500777606%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"img\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/pc41-e96a0c65d1a2ef1a2e1a18a6008d582f-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/pc41-e96a0c65d1a2ef1a2e1a18a6008d582f-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/pc41-e96a0c65d1a2ef1a2e1a18a6008d582f-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/pc41-e96a0c65d1a2ef1a2e1a18a6008d582f-48538.png 800w,\n/static/pc41-e96a0c65d1a2ef1a2e1a18a6008d582f-b70ec.png 1200w,\n/static/pc41-e96a0c65d1a2ef1a2e1a18a6008d582f-7e945.png 1286w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Then click <code class=\"language-text\">Add Local</code> and select <code class=\"language-text\">python</code> executable from the directory where you installed it.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>When you’re done, click <code class=\"language-text\">Create</code></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Now you should see something like this\n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/pc42-a7e0110c797940122355e12393a64971-1c089.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 67.6317743132888%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"img\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/pc42-a7e0110c797940122355e12393a64971-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/pc42-a7e0110c797940122355e12393a64971-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/pc42-a7e0110c797940122355e12393a64971-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/pc42-a7e0110c797940122355e12393a64971-48538.png 800w,\n/static/pc42-a7e0110c797940122355e12393a64971-b70ec.png 1200w,\n/static/pc42-a7e0110c797940122355e12393a64971-d134a.png 1600w,\n/static/pc42-a7e0110c797940122355e12393a64971-f6ead.png 2400w,\n/static/pc42-a7e0110c797940122355e12393a64971-1c089.png 2694w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Congrats! You’ve created your project in <code class=\"language-text\">PyCharm</code></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Adding your python script</h2>\n<p>Right click on your project name, then <code class=\"language-text\">New &gt; Python File</code>. Follow the pictures for better guidance.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/pc5-0cd3834e023169d3004261ee02e5ecf4-6f1e1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 46.70846394984326%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"img\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/pc5-0cd3834e023169d3004261ee02e5ecf4-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/pc5-0cd3834e023169d3004261ee02e5ecf4-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/pc5-0cd3834e023169d3004261ee02e5ecf4-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/pc5-0cd3834e023169d3004261ee02e5ecf4-48538.png 800w,\n/static/pc5-0cd3834e023169d3004261ee02e5ecf4-b70ec.png 1200w,\n/static/pc5-0cd3834e023169d3004261ee02e5ecf4-6f1e1.png 1276w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/pc6-b1c305230f77f843277b7bfbb0a3a38b-b629d.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 53.14533622559653%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"img\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/pc6-b1c305230f77f843277b7bfbb0a3a38b-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/pc6-b1c305230f77f843277b7bfbb0a3a38b-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/pc6-b1c305230f77f843277b7bfbb0a3a38b-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/pc6-b1c305230f77f843277b7bfbb0a3a38b-48538.png 800w,\n/static/pc6-b1c305230f77f843277b7bfbb0a3a38b-b629d.png 922w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>You don’t need to add any file extension, <code class=\"language-text\">PyCharm</code> will add it for you. Just name your file.</p>\n<h2>Running your script</h2>\n<p>Since you’re running the script for the very first time, you’ll need to add a <code class=\"language-text\">run config</code> for that script. Luckily, <code class=\"language-text\">PyCharm</code> does that automatically.</p>\n<p>While your script/ code file is open in the editor (double click to open if you’re on some other file) right click to bring up the context menu and then click <code class=\"language-text\">Run yourFile</code>. You can also use the keyboard shortcut.</p>\n<p>Once you run the file, the config gets added automatically. And from now, you can just click on the play icon on the menubar to run your code.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/pc7-842951bee83cde264517696c18cb2d51-ee537.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 62.522522522522515%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"img\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/pc7-842951bee83cde264517696c18cb2d51-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/pc7-842951bee83cde264517696c18cb2d51-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/pc7-842951bee83cde264517696c18cb2d51-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/pc7-842951bee83cde264517696c18cb2d51-48538.png 800w,\n/static/pc7-842951bee83cde264517696c18cb2d51-ee537.png 1110w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If you add another <code class=\"language-text\">python</code> script to your project and want to run it separately you’ll need to add a config for that as well. Just follow the same steps you did for the previous file.</p>\n<h2>Aaaaaand that’s it!</h2>","fields":{"slug":"/configure-pycharm/","prefix":"2018-11-21"},"frontmatter":{"title":"","author":null,"category":null,"cover":null}},"authornote":{"id":"e41d3786-42f8-581a-88e5-a557cd9179e3","html":"<p><strong>Shawon Ashraf</strong>  Hails from Dhaka, Bangladesh. A forever Java guy who’s tinkering with JavaScript and Swift these days. A long time RPG fan who plays Overwatch like frenzy these days. I like to talk\nanything *nix and OSS.</p>"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"facebook":{"appId":""}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/configure-pycharm/","next":{"id":"fa3a0623-c190-5229-b0bb-e9193e4c1dc4","fields":{"slug":"/cook-big-excel-py/","prefix":"2019-01-15","source":"posts"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Cooking big Excel files with Python and Openpyxl","category":"python"}},"source":"posts"}}